cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a method to improve the training of conditional generative adversarial networks (cGANs) by measuring the discrepancy between the data distribution and the model distribution on given samples. The proposed method is also applicable to computer vision (cs.CV) tasks as it involves generating images. Additionally, the paper mentions active learning (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) in the context of their proposed method. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to graphics (cs.GR) as it involves generating images.
